Ushabti-Hieroglyphs-Blue Faience-Late Period- 525-334 BCE

Case no.: 2

Accession Number:

Formal Label: Ushabti-Hieroglyphs-Blue Faience-Late Period- 525-334 BCE

Display Description:

This Ushabti of the Late Period has a Plain Lappet wig with 2 bands, plain plinth back-ten horizontal registers of hieroglyphs down the front and glazed in blue faience. The hands are crossed with sleeves with the right hand holding a holding a pick and the left holding a hoe.

LC Classification: DT62

Date or Time Horizon: Late period, 525-334 BCE.

Geographical Area: Saqqara, Egypt
